issue.body:
Wasn't sure if I should post here or on Onnx runtime … its over there...

https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/3428

body: If you have time pressure, could the PyTorch version help?https://pytorch.org/docs/stable/torchvision/models.html#torchvision.models.inception_v3

KeDengMS - thanks - I've grabbed the Inception model available in Keras/Tensorflow and have gotten that to work, including the conversion to ONNX.  So I will continue down that path.  However, I still have interest in being able to convert a few years worth of CNTK models (based on Inception) to ONNX if possible.

John and Ke,


I have a draft fix now. The root cause is that John is still using CNTK brain script which automatically adds sequence axis. Sequence axis is not supported in ONNX so I need to wrap some ops (pooling, conv, BN) with reshape ops.



To complete the work we need to follow the same process we did just 1 or 2 weeks ago. It involves other resources to test and build the nuget package. So let us collectively decide whether and how to proceed.



@JohnCrag in the mean time please migrate your models to CNTK V2 or better to Pytorch. ONNX feature in Pytorch is actively supported.



Thanks,

Liqun

I met the same problem. Has this problem been solved？

I see that on the nightly CNTK page there is mention of  2.8-rc0.dev20200502

But in VS2017, the NuGet Package Manager, with "include prereleases" checked does not offer it.  How to get it?  Perhaps it solves the problem that I've been waiting months for.  Very frustrating.

I just installed nightly package ...0509 in hope that this bug might be fixed.  But no,  still cannot convert an Inception-V3 model from CNTK to ONNX!    Catch this exception:

Error: two nodes with same node name (model.model.pool_2_Output_reshape_to_model.model.pool_2_Output_reshaped_for_conv).
